Current dev:mcp script: `bun --hot platform/mcp-server/dist/index.js --dev`

If dist/ doesn't exist, bun will throw a module resolution error that looks like a bug rather than a setup issue.

Create a small scripts/dev-mcp.ts:
```ts
import { resolve } from 'node:path';

const distPath = resolve(import.meta.dirname, '..', 'platform', 'mcp-server', 'dist', 'index.js');
const exists = await Bun.file(distPath).exists();

if (!exists) {
  console.error('Error: platform/mcp-server/dist/index.js not found.');
  console.error('Run `bun run build` first to compile the project.');
  process.exit(1);
}

// Re-exec with bun --hot
const proc = Bun.spawn(['bun', '--hot', distPath, '--dev'], {
  stdio: ['inherit', 'inherit', 'inherit'],
});
process.exit(await proc.exited);
```

Then update the dev:mcp script to: `bun scripts/dev-mcp.ts`

Make sure the new script file is covered by tsconfig.scripts.json (which covers scripts/*.ts files). Read tsconfig.scripts.json to confirm its include pattern.
